<%- include("partials/header") %>

<div class="top-pane">
  <div class="logo flex-item">
    <img class="logo-img" src="/images/books_icon.png" alt="Books_Logo"><p class="logo-heading">LMS</p>
  </div>
  <div class="admin-guide-btn">
    <a href="/guide/admin" class="admin-guide">Admin</a>
  </div>
  <hr class="hr-guide">
  <div class="other-guide-btn">
    <a href="/guide/others" class="other-guide current-active">Others</a>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="left-pane">
  <div class="flex-item flex-guide">
    <a href="#overview-guide" class="overview-guide">Overview</a>
  </div>
  <div class="flex-item flex-guide">
    <a href="#home-guide" class="home-guide">Home</a>
  </div>
  <div class="flex-item flex-guide">
    <a href="#books-guide" class="books-guide">Books</a>
    <ul class="list">
      <li><a href="#all-books-guide" class="all-books-guide">All Books</a></li>
      <li><a href="#my-books-guide" class="my-books-guide">My Books</a></li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  <div class="flex-item flex-guide">
    <a href="#requests-guide" class="requests-guide">Requests</a>
    <ul class="list">
      <li><a href="#request-book-guide" class="request-book-guide">Request a Book</a></li>
      <li><a href="#all-requests-guide" class="all-requests-guide">View Requests</a></li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  <div class="flex-item flex-guide">
    <a href="#my-info-guide" class="my-info-guide">My Info</a>
  </div>
</div>
<hr class="hr-content">

<div class="content">
  <div id="overview-guide" onmouseover="getId(this)" onmouseout="removeClass(this)">
    <h3>Overview</h3>
    <p>
      LMS stands for Library Management System. This guide will help the users to find out the functionalities available in this application. For each functionality, there is a designated section available in which the usage is mentioned along with some images.
    </p>
  </div>
  <hr class="separator">
  <div id="home-guide" onmouseover="getId(this)" onmouseout="removeClass(this)">
    <h3>Home</h3>
    <p>
      Home page lets the users to quickly peek into the list of available books present in the system, list of book requests that are raised by the particulare logged in user, latest books that are added to the system. On clicking the component in the Home Page, user will be redirected to the particular page which shows the detailed information about the respective component.
    </p>
    <img class="guide-img" src="/images/guide/homepageothers.png" alt="homepageothers">
  </div>
  <hr class="separator">
  <div id="books-guide" onmouseover="getId(this)" onmouseout="removeClass(this)">
    <h3>Books</h3>
    <p>
      This section consists of two sub categories in which users can able to view all the books issued to them, view all the books that are present in the system.
    </p>
    <div id="all-books-guide" onmouseover="getId(this)" onmouseout="removeClass(this)">
      <h3>All Books</h3>
      <p>
        All the books that are presently available in the system can be viewed from this page. There are two views available to check the list of books that are namely Grid and List. Clicking on the grid icon and hamburger icon will switch between views. Once the book has been issued to the user, he/she can never request the same book again until it is returned, the issue button will be grayed out until it is being returned to the Library.
      </p>
      <h4>Grid View</h4>
      <img class="guide-img" src="/images/guide/allbooksothers.png" alt="allbooksothers">
      <br>
      <br>
      <h4>List View</h4>
      <img class="guide-img" src="/images/guide/allbooksotherslist.png" alt="allbooksotherslist">
    </div>
    <br>
    <div id="my-books-guide" onmouseover="getId(this)" onmouseout="removeClass(this)">
      <h3>My Books</h3>
      <p>
        In this form, users can view the list of books that are issued to them from the Library. If the user wish to return the book back to the Library, they need to push the return button that is available for each book that are being displayed.
      </p>
      <img class="guide-img" src="/images/guide/mybooksothers.png" alt="mybooksothers">
    </div>
    <br>
  </div>
<hr class="separator">
<div id="requests-guide" onmouseover="getId(this)" onmouseout="removeClass(this)">
  <h3>Requests</h3>
  <br>
  <div id="request-book-guide" onmouseover="getId(this)" onmouseout="removeClass(this)">
    <h3>Request a Book</h3>
    <p>
      If a particular book is not available in the library then the user can raise a request to Admin to add the book to the Library. Users will get a message if the same book is being requested by another user or else, the book request will be submitted to the Admin.
    </p>
    <img class="guide-img" src="/images/guide/bookrequestothers.png" alt="bookrequestothers">
  </div>
  <br>
  <div id="all-requests-guide" onmouseover="getId(this)" onmouseout="removeClass(this)">
    <h3>View Requests</h3>
    <p>
      From this page, users can view the book requests that are raised by themselves. Also, the status of the book request will also be available for them to follow up.
    </p>
    <img class="guide-img" src="/images/guide/viewrequestsothers.png" alt="viewrequestsothers">
  </div>
</div>
<hr class="separator">
<div id="my-info-guide" onmouseover="getId(this)" onmouseout="removeClass(this)">
  <h3>My Info</h3>
  <p>
    This page will display the information about the logged in user. If the email address field is empty in this page then it is understood that the user have logged in using Google/Facebook/Twitter, users will get a tooltip about the same.
  </p>
  <img class="guide-img" src="/images/guide/myinfo.png" alt="myinfo">
</div>
<br>
<hr class="separator">
</div>

<%- include("partials/footer") %>
